that is actually sad :(

&gt; Could not find artifact pl.mycustom:core:jar:1.0 in central (https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2)

This one (according to naming convention) seems to be cached in your local ~/.m2/repository (or/and stored in the enterprise one) which is not available in docker container, i.e. if it stored in enterprise repository you need to setup maven in docker container (provide correct ~/.m2/setting.xml)

&gt; Could not find artifact org.testng:testng:jar:6.12 in central (https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2)

This one is even more problematic: testng-6.12 has never been deployed to maven central, but it seems there are plugin dependencies in you project which uses it :(

Could you tell what is your target goal? Just if you need to collect project&#39;s dependencies in single place and this is one-time activity is is possible to load dependencies from your ~/.m2/repository, smth. like:

1. setup ~/.m2/seettings.xml - set you local cache as a mirror
```
    &lt;mirrors&gt;
        &lt;mirror&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;internal-repository&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Dummy repository&lt;/name&gt;
            &lt;url&gt;!!!file:///Users/apanfilov/.m2/repository!!!&lt;/url&gt;
            &lt;mirrorOf&gt;*&lt;/mirrorOf&gt;
        &lt;/mirror&gt;
    &lt;/mirrors&gt;
```

